        <item>
            <title><![CDATA[peelSoN]]></title>
            <link>https://abhilashreddysh.github.io/wiki/blog/peelson</link>
            <guid>https://abhilashreddysh.github.io/wiki/blog/peelson</guid>
            <pubDate>Wed, 24 May 2023 00:00:00 GMT</pubDate>
            <description><![CDATA[Version - 3.0]]></description>
            <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Powershell script to prevent the system from going to sleep.Use this script to keep your computer awake by programmatically pressing the ScrollLock key every X seconds</p><div class="theme-admonition theme-admonition-info alert alert--info admonition_LlT9"><div class="admonitionHeading_tbUL"><span class="admonitionIcon_kALy"><svg viewBox="0 0 14 16"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M7 2.3c3.14 0 5.7 2.56 5.7 5.7s-2.56 5.7-5.7 5.7A5.71 5.71 0 0 1 1.3 8c0-3.14 2.56-5.7 5.7-5.7zM7 1C3.14 1 0 4.14 0 8s3.14 7 7 7 7-3.14 7-7-3.14-7-7-7zm1 3H6v5h2V4zm0 6H6v2h2v-2z"></path></svg></span>Version - 3.0</div><div class="admonitionContent_S0QG"><p><a href="https://github.com/abhilashreddysh/peelSoN" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Repository Link (This repository is private)</a></p><p>Version - 2.5
<a href="https://github.com/abhilashreddysh/AutomationScripts/blob/main/Powershell/peelSoN.ps1" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Single Script (Public)</a></p></div></div><h2 class="anchor anchorWithHideOnScrollNavbar_WYt5" id="single-script-public">Single script (Public)<a href="#single-script-public" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to Single script (Public)" title="Direct link to Single script (Public)">​</a></h2><p>Download the script and run in powershell. the script runs in an infinite loop. Click the icon in systemtray and explore more option to see what this script can do.</p><h2 class="anchor anchorWithHideOnScrollNavbar_WYt5" id="faq-repository">FAQ (Repository)<a href="#faq-repository" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to FAQ (Repository)" title="Direct link to FAQ (Repository)">​</a></h2><h3 class="anchor anchorWithHideOnScrollNavbar_WYt5" id="how-to-setup-">How to setup ?<a href="#how-to-setup-" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to How to setup ?" title="Direct link to How to setup ?">​</a></h3><h4 class="anchor anchorWithHideOnScrollNavbar_WYt5" id="using-script"><em>(Using Script)</em><a href="#using-script" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to using-script" title="Direct link to using-script">​</a></h4><p>Use initsetup.ps1 to setup and Change the task <em>peelSoN</em> trigger from (AtLogon) --&gt; (On Workstation Unlock) in task scheduler to start the script as soon as you login.</p><p>OR</p><h4 class="anchor anchorWithHideOnScrollNavbar_WYt5" id="manual-method"><em>(Manual Method)</em><a href="#manual-method" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to manual-method" title="Direct link to manual-method">​</a></h4><p>Download and save this folder with the name "peelSoN" in C:\temp and run start.vbs script. You can also automate the task by setting up a task in task scheduler to run on every given interval.</p><h3 class="anchor anchorWithHideOnScrollNavbar_WYt5" id="how-to-stop-the-running-session-">How to stop the running session ?<a href="#how-to-stop-the-running-session-" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to How to stop the running session ?" title="Direct link to How to stop the running session ?">​</a></h3><p>Every time the task is executed, a bat file is created on the desktop as killpeel.bat
Double click this bat file to kill the session and turn off peelSoN.</p><h3 class="anchor anchorWithHideOnScrollNavbar_WYt5" id="where-are-my-logs-saved-">Where are my logs saved ?<a href="#where-are-my-logs-saved-" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to Where are my logs saved ?" title="Direct link to Where are my logs saved ?">​</a></h3><p>Logs are saved at <code>C:\temp\peelSoN\logs</code></p><h3 class="anchor anchorWithHideOnScrollNavbar_WYt5" id="how-to-change-my-logout-time-">How to change my logout time ?<a href="#how-to-change-my-logout-time-" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to How to change my logout time ?" title="Direct link to How to change my logout time ?">​</a></h3><p>Edit the launch.bat file at <code>C:\temp\peelSoN\</code> and update the <code>Hour</code> and <code>Min</code> flag according to your needs.</p><div class="language-bat codeBlockContainer_Ckt0 theme-code-block" style="--prism-color:#F8F8F2;--prism-background-color:#282A36"><div class="codeBlockTitle_Ktv7">C:\temp\peelSoN\launch.bat</div><div class="codeBlockContent_biex"><pre tabindex="0" class="prism-code language-bat codeBlock_bY9V thin-scrollbar"><code class="codeBlockLines_e6Vv"><span class="token-line" style="color:#F8F8F2"><span class="token plain">Powershell.exe -File "C:\temp\peelSoN\peelson.ps1" -Hour 18 -Min 00 -sleep 120</span><br></span></code></pre><div class="buttonGroup__atx"><button type="button" aria-label="Copy code to clipboard" title="Copy" class="clean-btn"><span class="copyButtonIcons_eSgA" aria-hidden="true"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" class="copyButtonIcon_y97N"><path fill="currentColor" d="M19,21H8V7H19M19,5H8A2,2 0 0,0 6,7V21A2,2 0 0,0 8,23H19A2,2 0 0,0 21,21V7A2,2 0 0,0 19,5M16,1H4A2,2 0 0,0 2,3V17H4V3H16V1Z"></path></svg><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" class="copyButtonSuccessIcon_LjdS"><path fill="currentColor" d="M21,7L9,19L3.5,13.5L4.91,12.09L9,16.17L19.59,5.59L21,7Z"></path></svg></span></button></div></div></div><p>The above example stops the script at 18:00 (06:00 PM). <strong>You can also update the sleep timer</strong>.</p><h2 class="anchor anchorWithHideOnScrollNavbar_WYt5" id="changelog">Changelog<a href="#changelog" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to Changelog" title="Direct link to Changelog">​</a></h2><div class="theme-admonition theme-admonition-info alert alert--info admonition_LlT9"><div class="admonitionHeading_tbUL"><span class="admonitionIcon_kALy"><svg viewBox="0 0 14 16"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M7 2.3c3.14 0 5.7 2.56 5.7 5.7s-2.56 5.7-5.7 5.7A5.71 5.71 0 0 1 1.3 8c0-3.14 2.56-5.7 5.7-5.7zM7 1C3.14 1 0 4.14 0 8s3.14 7 7 7 7-3.14 7-7-3.14-7-7-7zm1 3H6v5h2V4zm0 6H6v2h2v-2z"></path></svg></span>info</div><div class="admonitionContent_S0QG"><p>Version 2.x is a single script version which should be manually triggered</p><p>Version 3.x is fully automated which include initial setup, auto triggering based on the time set to logoff, and auto updates.</p></div></div><h3 class="anchor anchorWithHideOnScrollNavbar_WYt5" id="30">3.0<a href="#30" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to 3.0" title="Direct link to 3.0">​</a></h3><ul><li>Script will run anonymously and generate a bat file on desktop to kill it.</li><li>Auto install script and setup a task</li></ul><h3 class="anchor anchorWithHideOnScrollNavbar_WYt5" id="25">2.5<a href="#25" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to 2.5" title="Direct link to 2.5">​</a></h3><ul><li>Added Context Menu to run in systemtray</li></ul><h3 class="anchor anchorWithHideOnScrollNavbar_WYt5" id="24">2.4<a href="#24" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to 2.4" title="Direct link to 2.4">​</a></h3><ul><li>Script will now end after the logout time</li></ul>]]></content:encoded>
            <author>abhilashreddysh.99@gmail.com (Abhilash Reddy)</author>
